    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Injuries Will Result</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Constance Pond says plan to keep subway doors open no more than 45 seconds may cause accidents (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To The Editor:</p>
        <p>Keeping subway doors open no more than 45 seconds (news article, Nov. 12) seems like a recipe for disaster for parents and their small children and for the elderly. The closing doors may separate children from parents and may cause older people injury. I hope this is not brought into common use as a way to improve our transit system.</p>
        <p>CONSTANCE POND</p>
        <p>New York, Nov. 14, 1996</p>
      </block>
